Summary points
• The Harvard and Australian studies of medical error are the only studies that provide population data on the rates of injuries of patients in hospitals, and they identified a substantial amount of medical error
• In the United States, medical error results in 44,000 to 98,000 unnecessary deaths each year and 1 million excess injuries
• Errors often occur when clinicians are inexperienced and new procedures are introduced
• Extremes of age, complex care, and a prolonged hospital stay are associated with more errors
